      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LONG SERVICE LEAF (3) got over the top to score on resumption as an odds-on pop, winning by 0.3L over this track and trip 10 days ago. He went to a new level there and he looks ready to raise the bar again this time around. He's unbeaten at this track and trip and can go on with the job. HOT SEA (5) debuted in G3 company as a 2YO before missing as a $1.14 favourite in his only start last campaign at Moe. The form out of that worked out well though and his latest Lark Hill trial was solid. Can sit handy and shed the maiden tag. PAINT IT RED (6) returned with a bang when being too speedy over this trip at Ascot 24 days ago. Pike hops on board now and she should be better for that effort. Wouldn't surprise to see her repeat the dose. ETERNAL WINE (4) can pick up from where he left off. BABY PEARL (1) is not to be discounted after a narrow win here last week.",
